  "name": "Manganese Floor",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": ["Obrix"],
  "description": "The mineral plain of the deep ocean floor, covered in nodule deposits. Three LP processors chain together to enforce maximum depth: proc1 (120 Hz), proc2 (280 Hz), proc3 (600 Hz) — a cascading low-pass architecture that strips away everything above the fundamental. Triangle src1 offers its soft harmonics for the chain to consume; Sine src2 anchors the sub. Journey Mode holds the field open at distance=0.9, the second deepest distance in this collection. Four mods — LFO->FilterCutoff (proc1 slowly sweeps), Env->Volume (bloom and settle), Velocity->FilterCutoff (proc2 responds), Aftertouch->FXMix (spatial expansion) — barely disturb the geological stasis.",
